  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across 5 flow-speed combinations. All 13 credibility factors are assessed and required levels are met or exceeded under the declared operating description; the package is accepted. The ContextOfUse description enumerates temperature (35–38 °C), inlet gauge pressure (−10 to +20 mmHg), outlet gauge pressure (60–120 mmHg), and flow regime (laminar-to-transitional, Re 200–3 500) in narrative form, giving the appearance of a fully bounded envelope.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cou2-vad-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-vad-hemolysis-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump",
  "bindsDataset": [
